Subject: [PATCH] Allow embedder-registered schemes to host service workers (GLib API opt-in)

Widen the WebCore http/https gate in ServiceWorkerContainer::addRegistration so a
secure origin whose scheme the EMBEDDER explicitly registered as SW-capable may
host a service worker, and expose that opt-in through WebKitGTK's
WebKitSecurityManager, mirroring the existing register_uri_scheme_as_secure /
_is_secure surface. This is an OPT-IN policy relaxation (default-off), NOT a
blanket one: only a scheme the app registered is admitted.

Context: wezig ADR-0016 (github.com/wighawag/wezig). Corroborating demand:
github.com/tauri-apps/tauri#13031 ("status: upstream").

Sized/located against WebKit main (commit-agnostic; predicates verified 2026-07-19):
  Source/WebCore/workers/service/ServiceWorkerContainer.cpp  (2 predicate widenings)
  Source/WebCore/platform/LegacySchemeRegistry.{h,cpp}       (registry pair)
  Source/WebKit/UIProcess/API/glib/WebKitSecurityManager.{h,cpp}  (GLib API glue)
  Source/WebKit/UIProcess/WebProcessPool.{h,cpp}             (UI->Web IPC sync)
  Source/WebKit/WebProcess/WebProcess.{messages.in,cpp}      (Web-process receiver)

This is a LOCATE+SIZE draft against upstream paths (the dev box cannot build
WebKitGTK; see the findings note). Line numbers are approximate; the two WebCore
predicates and the mirrored GLib/registry/IPC layers are the load-bearing edits.
The build-and-measure follow-on rebases this onto the exact tagged tree it builds.

